<td data-index="731"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p data-index="732">At the end of 2021 (the second year), the difference between the book basis and the tax basis of the accounts receivable is $10,000. Chelsea multiplies this difference by the applicable tax rate to arrive at the deferred tax liability of $2,000 ($10,000 × .20), which it reports at the end of 2021. Income taxes payable for 2021 is $18,000 (<a href="#c19-fig-3" data-index="733" data-section-index="29" data-section-idref="c19-fig-3" data-target-data-index="232">Illustration 19.3</a>), and the income tax expense for 2021 is as shown in <a class="blue" href="#c19-fig-10" id="c19-fig-10-1" data-index="734" data-section-index="29" data-section-idref="c19-fig-10" data-target-data-index="736"><b data-index="735">Illustration 19.10</b></a>.</p>
