<figcaption data-index="1401"><p data-index="1402"><span class="figureLabel" data-index="1403"><b data-index="1404"><a role="doc-backlink" href="#c19-fig-20-1" data-index="1405" data-section-index="29" data-section-idref="c19-fig-20-1" data-target-data-index="1375"><span style=" background-color: #226C7B; color: #FFFFFF;" data-index="1406">ILLUSTRATION 19.20</span></a></b> <b data-index="1407">Schedule of Future Deductible Amounts</b></span></p></figcaption>
</figure>
<p data-index="1408">Assuming that 2020 is Hunt's first year of operations and income taxes payable is $100,000, Hunt computes its income tax expense as shown in <a class="blue" href="#c19-fig-21" id="c19-fig-21-1" data-index="1409" data-section-index="29" data-section-idref="c19-fig-21" data-target-data-index="1411"><b data-index="1410">Illustration 19.21</b></a>.</p>
