<h4 data-index="3339"><span class="codeColorBlue3" data-index="3340">Carryforward with Valuation Allowance</span></h4>
<p data-index="3341">Let us return to the Groh example. Assume that it is more likely than not that Groh will <i data-index="3342">not</i> realize the entire NOL carryforward in future years. In this situation, Groh records a <span epub:type="pagebreak" role="doc-pagebreak" title="19-21" id="Page_19-21" data-index="3343"></span>Deferred Tax Asset of $40,000 ($200,000 × .20) for the potential benefits related to the loss carryforward, and an allowance to reduce the deferred tax asset by the same amount. Groh makes the following journal entries in 2020.</p>
