</figure>
<p data-index="4274">Income tax expense (or benefit) generally equals the sum of income taxes payable (or refundable) and the change in the deferred tax expense or benefit. The formula in <a class="blue" href="#c19-fig-46" id="c19-fig-46-1" data-index="4275" data-section-index="29" data-section-idref="c19-fig-46" data-target-data-index="4277"><b data-index="4276">Illustration 19.46</b></a> is used to compute income tax expense (benefit).</p>
<figure id="c19-fig-46" data-index="4277">
<table class="table" style=" background-color: #E2F4FD;" data-index="4278">
<tbody data-index="4279">
<tr data-index="4280">
